# API Rule

- Centralize HTTP configuration in a single Axios client module.
- Wrap every API call with base error handling:
  - catch transport errors
  - normalize status/message
  - return typed safe result or throw typed error
- Define TypeScript types/interfaces for every request/response payload.
- Keep endpoint functions small and single-purpose.
- No direct fetch/axios usage in UI components; consume only api functions.
- Add JSDoc or TS docs for side effects and expected failures.

## Example Pattern

```ts
type BookingResponse = { id: string; status: "booked" | "cancelled" };

export async function createBooking(payload: CreateBookingInput): Promise<BookingResponse> {
  try {
    const { data } = await apiClient.post<BookingResponse>("/bookings", payload);
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    throw normalizeApiError(error);
  }
}
```
